	<!-- Factors That Affect Cost -->
	<section class="cost-factors">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>What Affects House Cleaning Cost in Knoxville?</h2>
			<p class="section-intro">Understanding these factors helps you get an accurate estimate and potentially save money on your cleaning service.</p>

			<div class="factors-grid">
				<div class="factor-card">
					<div class="factor-icon">📏</div>
					<h3>Home Size</h3>
					<p>This is the most significant cost factor. Larger homes require more time, more cleaning supplies, and often multiple cleaners. A 1,000 sq ft apartment takes 2-3 hours to deep clean, while a 3,000 sq ft home may take 6-8 hours.</p>
					<p class="factor-tip"><strong>Money-saving tip:</strong> Focus on high-priority areas if you're on a tight budget - you can request certain rooms only.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="factor-card">
					<div class="factor-icon">🚪</div>
					<h3>Number of Rooms & Bathrooms</h3>
					<p>Bathrooms and kitchens require more detailed cleaning than bedrooms or living areas. A 2,000 sq ft home with 4 bathrooms costs more to clean than the same size home with 2 bathrooms.</p>
					<p class="factor-tip"><strong>Money-saving tip:</strong> Keep bathrooms maintained between professional cleanings to reduce time needed.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="factor-card featured-factor">
					<div class="factor-icon">📅</div>
					<h3>Cleaning Frequency</h3>
					<p>Recurring service is significantly cheaper than one-time cleaning. When your home is cleaned regularly, it stays in better condition and requires less time per visit.</p>
