			<div class="pricing-comparison-detailed">
				<div class="pricing-model-card">
					<h3>Hourly Pricing</h3>
					<p class="model-rate">$18-$25/hour per cleaner</p>
					<p class="model-description">You're charged based on how long the cleaning takes. Most companies send 2-3 cleaners for 2-4 hours.</p>

					<h4>Pros:</h4>
					<ul class="pros-list">
						<li>Seems flexible at first glance</li>
						<li>Can work for very small or unusual jobs</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Cons:</h4>
					<ul class="cons-list">
						<li>Unpredictable total cost - you won't know the final price until they're done</li>
						<li>No incentive for cleaners to work efficiently</li>
						<li>Easy for time to expand beyond estimates</li>
						<li>Can feel awkward monitoring how long cleaners take</li>
						<li>Often ends up costing more than expected</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="example-box">
						<strong>Example:</strong> You're quoted "2-3 hours with 2 cleaners" at $20/hour = $80-$120 estimate. But what if it takes 4 hours? Now you're at $160 - and you had no control over it.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="pricing-model-card featured-model">
					<h3>Flat Rate Pricing (Hero's Model)</h3>
					<p class="model-rate">Set price per job</p>
					<p class="model-description">You receive an exact price quote before service based on your home size, condition, and service type. That's what you pay - no surprises.</p>

					<h4>Pros:</h4>
					<ul class="pros-list">
						<li><strong>Know exact cost upfront</strong> - no surprises or bill shock</li>
						<li>Cleaners work efficiently to complete the job well</li>
						<li>Budget-friendly and predictable</li>
						<li>No awkward time-watching or wondering about the final bill</li>
						<li>Fair to both customer and cleaner</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Cons:</h4>
					<ul class="cons-list">
						<li>Honestly? We can't think of any (when priced fairly)</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="example-box highlight">
						<strong>Example:</strong> You get a quote for $200 for a deep clean. Whether it takes 3 hours or 4.5 hours, you pay $200. You know exactly what to budget, and our team focuses on quality, not clock-watching.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="why-flat-rate">
				<h3>Why We Use Flat Rate Pricing</h3>
